00:10:21.470 --> 00:10:24.720
Kita-chan

00:10:24.720 --> 00:10:27.730
Kita-chan

00:10:27.730 --> 00:10:29.730
Kita-chan

00:10:32.730 --> 00:10:35.730
Kita-chan

00:10:53.720 --> 00:10:56.510
Excuse me. Trainer-san?

00:10:56.510 --> 00:11:00.270
Hey, Kitasan. Good work today. What's up?

00:11:00.270 --> 00:11:04.680
The campfire is about to start. Golshi-san and
the others said to bring you in.

00:11:04.680 --> 00:11:07.210
They just want to sponge off me
before it's all over.

00:11:07.210 --> 00:11:09.690
Not that I have any money to share.

00:11:11.090 --> 00:11:11.930
Huh?

00:11:12.350 --> 00:11:13.940
Are those me?

00:11:13.940 --> 00:11:16.690
Y-Yeah, I was just taking a look.

00:11:17.230 --> 00:11:18.760
That's my debut race!

00:11:17.250 --> 00:11:19.260
Debut Race (Rookie Debut)

00:11:19.210 --> 00:11:21.050
2nd Race

00:11:19.400 --> 00:11:23.990
And this is my second, and this is
when I was in the Spring Stakes...

00:11:21.090 --> 00:11:23.990
Spring Stakes

00:11:23.990 --> 00:11:27.930
I never thought you'd be going into the
Classics after three wins in a row.

00:11:28.850 --> 00:11:32.420
I still wasn't too popular back then, though.

00:11:32.440 --> 00:11:38.920
Satsukishou

00:11:32.900 --> 00:11:34.870
The Satsukishou and Derby...

00:11:35.450 --> 00:11:38.410
Those were both so hard and painful.

00:11:37.230 --> 00:11:38.920
Japan Derby

00:11:39.230 --> 00:11:42.180
But you were able to get over what happened.

00:11:42.180 --> 00:11:45.930
St. Lite Kinen

00:11:42.820 --> 00:11:45.930
At the St. Lite Kinen, and then...

00:11:44.780 --> 00:11:45.930
Kikkashou

00:11:46.250 --> 00:11:47.430
The Kikkashou.

00:11:51.470 --> 00:11:53.810
The Arima Kinen and the Osaka Hai,

00:11:53.810 --> 00:11:57.550
and my first Spring Tennoushou,
and the Takarazuka Kinen...

00:11:57.550 --> 00:12:01.660
You were favored to win for the first
time at the Tokyo Daishouten, right?

00:12:01.660 --> 00:12:05.320
I felt weirdly nervous about it, too.

00:12:05.320 --> 00:12:07.830
Japan Cup

00:12:05.920 --> 00:12:10.730
Then I won the Japan Cup, and raced
against Dia-chan at my second Arima...

00:12:07.830 --> 00:12:11.330
Arima Kinen

00:12:12.070 --> 00:12:15.210
I've run so, so much.

00:12:15.730 --> 00:12:18.210
Yeah, you have.

00:12:18.650 --> 00:12:21.400
And next is the Takarazuka.

00:12:21.790 --> 00:12:22.540
Right.

00:12:23.680 --> 00:12:27.850
No horse girl has ever won
the Spring Senior Series Triple Crown.

00:12:28.350 --> 00:12:32.890
You've been in a lot of exhausting
races, but I bet you can pull it off.

00:12:36.170 --> 00:12:37.320
Trainer-san.

00:12:38.190 --> 00:12:43.360
I'm going to win the Takarazuka Kinen.
And then I want to take on a new challenge!

00:12:43.770 --> 00:12:44.810
Overseas!

00:12:45.990 --> 00:12:48.120
I've thought about it a lot.

00:12:48.460 --> 00:12:53.930
About what I can do to
make people even happier.

00:12:54.870 --> 00:12:58.450
People's hopes and wishes,
their expectations and dreams...

00:12:58.810 --> 00:13:01.850
I want to carry them all, run,

00:13:01.850 --> 00:13:05.620
and be the first one to cross
the goal, so I can answer them.

00:13:06.680 --> 00:13:13.080
Burn, burn, fire burn!

00:13:07.390 --> 00:13:12.680
So that everyone will be smiling, happy,
and making noise, like at a festival.

00:13:13.100 --> 00:13:17.690
I feel like... I feel like I can
see a scene like that unfolding!

00:13:19.690 --> 00:13:20.790
I see...

00:13:21.450 --> 00:13:22.690
Okay, then.

00:13:23.200 --> 00:13:26.160
I'll start the process of registering
you for the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe.

00:13:27.170 --> 00:13:28.710
Thank you so much!

00:13:28.710 --> 00:13:30.340
Okay, Trainer-san!

00:13:30.340 --> 00:13:35.410
The campfire is starting!
Everyone's waiting, so hurry along!

00:13:41.000 --> 00:13:45.010
Umamusume

00:13:41.000 --> 00:13:45.010
Pretty Derby

00:13:45.450 --> 00:13:48.260
Really?! You're going to run at
the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe?

00:13:48.560 --> 00:13:50.890
Yeah, I thought about it a lot.

00:13:51.110 --> 00:13:54.110
Well, you had better get over
your cold even faster, then!

00:13:54.110 --> 00:13:54.890
Yeah.

00:13:54.890 --> 00:13:57.040
I think it might be built up exhaustion.

00:13:57.040 --> 00:13:59.200
You probably let your guard
down after the event was over.

00:13:59.200 --> 00:14:00.650
You might be right.

00:14:01.130 --> 00:14:02.670
Well, I'm gonna head out.

00:14:02.670 --> 00:14:03.850
See you later.

00:14:04.230 --> 00:14:06.050
Thank you for everything.

00:14:12.170 --> 00:14:14.250
What's going on with her?

00:14:14.250 --> 00:14:16.910
I think... she might be quitting.

00:14:17.560 --> 00:14:19.960
It's not that strange to
leave the turf for good

00:14:19.960 --> 00:14:21.930
after you feel you've gone as far as you can.

00:14:22.420 --> 00:14:23.670
I see...

00:14:25.940 --> 00:14:29.680
Anyway, you should make sure to
rest up and get better soon. Okay?

00:14:29.680 --> 00:14:31.850
Oh, Dia-chan.

00:14:33.020 --> 00:14:35.590
There was something I wanted to borrow.

00:14:37.290 --> 00:14:39.100
"The Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe."

00:14:39.100 --> 00:14:50.280
Satono Family Property

00:14:39.590 --> 00:14:44.970
"A race held in France, featuring
international Derby Horse Girls and

00:14:44.970 --> 00:14:50.280
the top class of G1 horse girls, considered to
be one of the greatest in the world."

00:14:50.280 --> 00:14:57.680
Japanese horse girls who have competed
in the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe

00:14:50.280 --> 00:15:02.290
Sirius Symboli

00:14:50.280 --> 00:15:02.290
El Condor Pasa

00:14:50.280 --> 00:15:02.290
Manhattan Cafe

00:14:50.280 --> 00:15:02.290
Nakayama Festa

00:14:50.610 --> 00:14:53.620
"Several Japanese horse girls
have attempted, and failed,

00:14:53.620 --> 00:14:56.250
this battle to determine
the greatest in the world."

00:14:53.890 --> 00:15:02.290
Gold Ship

00:14:56.250 --> 00:14:58.210
"To win this race would effectively

00:14:58.210 --> 00:15:02.290
alter the course of Japanese
horse girl history," huh?

00:15:02.900 --> 00:15:07.250
One of the greatest races in the world...
it really must be amazing.

00:15:08.700 --> 00:15:10.800
If I could run in it...

00:15:11.200 --> 00:15:13.410
No, I have to win!

00:15:15.660 --> 00:15:17.470
Okay!

00:15:17.470 --> 00:15:19.750
Sorry for worrying you!

00:15:19.750 --> 00:15:21.500
Are you feeling better?

00:15:21.500 --> 00:15:23.390
Yep! All better!

00:15:23.390 --> 00:15:26.230
Don't overdo it. You don't wanna
aggravate that bug you had.

00:15:26.230 --> 00:15:29.900
It's okay! All it took was a
day of rest to feel better!

00:15:29.900 --> 00:15:32.740
Now I need to run to make up
for what I missed yesterday!

00:15:48.880 --> 00:15:52.150
You were just sick, so please,
don't overexert yourself.

00:15:52.150 --> 00:15:53.430
R-Right.

00:15:53.430 --> 00:15:57.850
But I need to work hard if I want to
cause a festival wave all over Japan!

00:15:57.850 --> 00:15:59.580
A festival wave?

00:15:59.580 --> 00:16:01.770
Yeah! A festival wave!

00:16:02.080 --> 00:16:05.150
Okay! I'm gonna go for one more!

00:16:05.150 --> 00:16:05.800
Wait!

00:16:08.220 --> 00:16:10.400
Kitasan wants to race overseas?

00:16:10.400 --> 00:16:11.550
Yeah...

00:16:11.550 --> 00:16:15.560
You don't seem excited about the
prospect. Is there a problem?

00:16:15.560 --> 00:16:20.410
She seems to be up to the challenge, in
terms of accomplishments and strength.

00:16:21.740 --> 00:16:23.700
I'm honestly kinda worried.

00:16:23.700 --> 00:16:26.520
We're talking about traveling distances
that nothing in Japan compares to.

00:16:26.520 --> 00:16:30.260
There's compatibility issues between the
turf over there and Japanese horse girls.

00:16:30.600 --> 00:16:34.800
Not to mention, we'd be
relying a lot on a local trainer.

00:16:35.080 --> 00:16:38.780
You hear a lot of cases where they race too
frequently when not used to running overseas,

00:16:38.780 --> 00:16:43.180
which ends up resulting in an
overall decrease in ability.

00:16:43.640 --> 00:16:44.790
There's also...

00:16:47.130 --> 00:16:48.940
No, nevermind.

00:16:49.690 --> 00:16:53.820
Get a grip, all right?! You can't
be the one freaking out.

00:16:54.160 --> 00:16:57.590
Yeah, you'd have to be God to
know what the right answer is

00:16:57.590 --> 00:16:59.910
before the question even comes up.

00:17:01.530 --> 00:17:05.680
If you need advice about overseas racing,
wouldn't she be the one to ask?

00:17:05.680 --> 00:17:07.830
Sorry I'm late!

00:17:07.830 --> 00:17:10.270
Welcome to the party. What'll you have?

00:17:10.270 --> 00:17:11.880
Let's see...

00:17:11.880 --> 00:17:13.470
They've got milk, too.

00:17:15.490 --> 00:17:16.340
In that case...

00:17:16.920 --> 00:17:19.110
I'll have tequila, straight,
in a stein, please.

00:17:35.030 --> 00:17:36.320
Summit
of
Mount
Ashigara

00:17:35.030 --> 00:17:36.320
Enjoy
the
natural
beauty
of
Mount
Ashigara

00:17:41.830 --> 00:17:45.020
This will bring the spring G1
races for this year to a close,

00:17:45.020 --> 00:17:47.000
in the grand prix known
as the Takarazuka Kinen.

00:17:47.000 --> 00:17:48.630
It's nearly time to run!

00:17:49.080 --> 00:17:51.610
And the overwhelming favorite to win

00:17:51.610 --> 00:17:54.130
is number one in the
fan vote, Kitasan Black.

00:17:54.420 --> 00:17:56.670
After winning the Osaka Hai and
the Spring Tennoushou,

00:17:56.670 --> 00:17:58.950
this is her chance to win the
Senior Class Triple Crown.

00:17:58.950 --> 00:18:02.010
It should be quite the sight to see
what kind of race she's going to run.

00:18:02.490 --> 00:18:06.020
I'm gonna win this race,
and then head to France!

00:18:06.310 --> 00:18:08.520
My first domestic G1 win...

00:18:08.740 --> 00:18:10.240
Today's the day!

00:18:10.970 --> 00:18:12.560
I'm gonna win.

00:18:12.560 --> 00:18:15.990
I don't want to feel so
disappointed in myself ever again.

00:18:16.230 --> 00:18:18.530
I need to win this, no matter what!

00:18:22.870 --> 00:18:27.450
Kitasan Black is entering
the gate, looking calm.

00:18:28.590 --> 00:18:31.000
And last is Satono Crown.

00:18:31.000 --> 00:18:33.500
Coming to you from the Hanshin Racecourse,
just after some rain, at the grand prix!

00:18:35.530 --> 00:18:36.770
And they're off!

00:18:36.770 --> 00:18:38.620
The horse girls are lined
up next to each other now,

00:18:38.620 --> 00:18:40.510
and Kitasan Black is off to a good start!

00:18:42.760 --> 00:18:44.140
We've got a struggle for first place.

00:18:44.440 --> 00:18:46.170
Flying Turkey is looking for a spot...

00:18:46.170 --> 00:18:49.290
And it looks like Cheval
Grand has taken the initiative!

00:18:50.730 --> 00:18:53.140
She's being rather bold here!

00:18:53.140 --> 00:18:56.810
And behind her is Xbalanque,
followed by Kitasan Black!

00:18:56.810 --> 00:18:58.070
She's taken a good position here!

00:18:58.070 --> 00:18:59.370
Cheval-chan?

00:18:59.860 --> 00:19:02.200
No, I need to focus on my own race!

00:19:02.200 --> 00:19:04.250
On the inside is Ribon Gavotte,

00:19:04.250 --> 00:19:06.930
with All Haiyu near the middle of
the pack, along with Satono Crown.

00:19:06.930 --> 00:19:09.730
Ribon Pastoral is on the outside
along with Seventh Queen,

00:19:09.730 --> 00:19:13.880
followed by Brave Target and Original Shine,
with the first corner coming up!

00:19:14.320 --> 00:19:15.840
Cheval Grand has taken the lead,

00:19:15.840 --> 00:19:18.840
and only she knows how she
plans for this to play out!

00:19:19.230 --> 00:19:21.010
Kitasan Black may have missed
out on an early top spot,

00:19:21.220 --> 00:19:24.850
but she'll be looking to hold strong
and earn that third spring G1 win.

00:19:24.850 --> 00:19:27.580
The horse girls are crossing the
opposite side of the course.

00:19:27.580 --> 00:19:30.310
Cheval Grand is still in the
lead as she boldly rushes on.

00:19:30.310 --> 00:19:32.160
A half-length behind is Xbalanque,

00:19:32.160 --> 00:19:34.770
and then on the outside is
Kitasan Black in third place.

00:19:34.770 --> 00:19:36.570
Satono Crown is also in contention!

00:19:38.820 --> 00:19:40.520
Kita-san's not making her move.

00:19:40.520 --> 00:19:41.370
She's not.

00:19:41.370 --> 00:19:43.560
That ain't quite like her, huh?

00:19:43.560 --> 00:19:46.310
I'm sure she's fine! It's Kita-san.

00:19:46.870 --> 00:19:49.450
The first 1,000 meters are crossed
in one minute and .06 seconds.

00:19:49.450 --> 00:19:51.390
A slightly faster pace than last year.

00:19:50.110 --> 00:19:53.120
Okay, the time to move... is now!

00:19:55.340 --> 00:19:58.880
Entering the third corner, the pace
seems to have become steady,

00:19:58.880 --> 00:20:01.930
but Cheval Grand is still in the lead,
with Xbalanque on the outside!

00:20:01.930 --> 00:20:03.240
And then there's Kitasan Black!

00:20:03.240 --> 00:20:06.260
When will she make her move, and how will
she overwhelm the other horse girls?

00:20:07.000 --> 00:20:08.260
Huh?

00:20:09.290 --> 00:20:12.750
Not yet! Kitasan Black isn't taking off yet!

00:20:12.750 --> 00:20:14.530
Meanwhile, Cheval Grand
gradually pushes forward.

00:20:14.530 --> 00:20:17.460
And from the outside, Satono Crown
and Original Shine are moving up!

00:20:17.460 --> 00:20:19.530
Not only that, but All Haiyu
is closing in on the inside!

00:20:22.570 --> 00:20:24.710
They've all gathered up now!

00:20:24.710 --> 00:20:27.700
The horse girls are racing side by side
as they go around the final corner!

00:20:27.700 --> 00:20:30.700
Kitasan Black is holding steady
while heading to the straight!

00:20:28.990 --> 00:20:30.700
Go, Kitasan!

00:20:32.810 --> 00:20:34.470
Xbalanque is now in the lead!

00:20:34.470 --> 00:20:37.200
Satono Crown and Kitasan Black
are making gains on the outside!

00:20:37.200 --> 00:20:41.630
They're in the final straight now. Will Kitasan
Black be able to rush on to the goal?!

00:20:45.510 --> 00:20:47.760
Look at that! Kitasan Black is struggling!

00:20:48.030 --> 00:20:52.560
She's not gaining! At all! We're seeing
a lack of her usual power!

00:20:52.560 --> 00:20:53.770
Why!?

00:20:53.770 --> 00:20:57.280
And now it's Satono Crown who
is steadily gaining ground!

00:20:57.280 --> 00:20:59.210
While Kitasan Black has stopped accelerating!

00:20:59.210 --> 00:21:02.830
Kitasan Black was heavily
favored but is sinking!

00:21:02.830 --> 00:21:05.240
And as if to take her place,
Satono Crown is blazing ahead!

00:21:05.570 --> 00:21:07.930
She passes! Satono Crown!

00:21:07.930 --> 00:21:11.770
On the inside you can see All Haiyu,
and further in, Seventh Queen is also moving up!

00:21:11.770 --> 00:21:14.320
But they just can't beat Satono Crown!

00:21:14.320 --> 00:21:17.620
She's accelerating as if to
shut down any contenders!

00:21:17.620 --> 00:21:20.330
Satono Crown! It's Satono Crown!

00:21:20.330 --> 00:21:23.090
Satono Crown crosses the goal in first place!

00:21:25.090 --> 00:21:29.190
Second goes to All Haiyu,
and third to Seventh Queen.

00:21:28.590 --> 00:21:30.600
Summit
of
Mount
Ashigara

00:21:28.590 --> 00:21:30.600
Enjoy
the
natural
beauty
of
Mount
Ashigara

00:21:29.190 --> 00:21:32.210
What a showing by Satono Crown!

00:21:32.210 --> 00:21:34.920
Kitasan Black has been defeated!

00:21:41.530 --> 00:21:42.790
I did it...

00:21:45.930 --> 00:21:47.320
I did it!

00:21:47.320 --> 00:21:49.570
I really did it!

00:21:49.570 --> 00:21:52.990
Congratulations, Crown-san!

00:22:08.440 --> 00:22:09.340
Huh?

00:22:13.570 --> 00:22:14.660
Wha...

00:22:16.210 --> 00:22:17.520
Huh?

